---
const filters = [
  { id: 'all', label: 'All' },
  { id: 'web', label: 'Web' },
  { id: 'mobile', label: 'Mobile' },
  { id: 'cloud', label: 'Cloud' },
  { id: 'data', label: 'Data' },
  { id: 'ai', label: 'AI' },
  { id: 'devsecops', label: 'SRE / Sec' },
  { id: 'microsoft', label: 'Microsoft' },
];
---

<section id="technologies" class="section-y">
  <div class="container-zen flex flex-col gap-12 lg:flex-row lg:gap-16">
    <div class="max-w-sm shrink-0 lg:pt-2">
      <p class="eyebrow text-violet-200/50">Toolkit</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">Stack signals</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-500">
        Filters are a shorthand—not an exhaustive list. If your stack is adjacent, we have probably touched something
        close to it in production.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 border-b border-white/[0.06] pb-6">
        {
          filters.map((f, i) => (
            <button
              type="button"
              onclick={`showTechCategory('${f.id}', this)`}
              class:list={['tech-filter cursor-pointer text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide', i === 0 ? 'pill-active' : 'pill']}
            >
              {f.label}
            </button>
          ))
        }
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="tech-category web surface p-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Web &amp; APIs</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Component models, SSR/SSG hybrids, and API surfaces that stay coherent as teams grow.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">React</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Next.js</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Vue</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Astro</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Node.js</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-category mobile surface p-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Mobile</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Ship once, tune per platform where native behavior matters.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">React Native</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Flutter</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">iOS</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Android</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">PWA</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-category cloud devsecops surface p-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Cloud &amp; runtime</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Kubernetes when it earns its keep; managed services when they do not.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">AWS</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Azure</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">GCP</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Docker</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Kubernetes</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-category data ai surface p-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Data stores</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Operational correctness first; analytics paths second.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">PostgreSQL</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">MySQL</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">MongoDB</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Redis</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-category ai surface p-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">ML in production</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Evaluation harnesses, retrieval patterns, and cost-aware inference.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Python</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">NLP</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Vector DB</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">MLOps</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-category devsecops surface p-7">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">SRE &amp; security</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">Pipelines, policy-as-code, and telemetry that shortens incidents.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">GitHub Actions</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Terraform</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Ansible</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">OpenTelemetry</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tech-category microsoft surface p-7 sm:col-span-2">
          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">Microsoft landscape</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-500">.NET services, Entra-shaped identity, and Azure DevOps workflows for regulated environments.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="pill !normal-case">.NET</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">C#</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Azure DevOps</span>
            <span class="pill !normal-case">Entra ID</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
